<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/632> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #632" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.9.1; Diod. 16.6.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -St]olo; S.'s name entire); Chr. 354 (Stolo et Uetico); Fast. Hyd. (Stollone et Petino), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 105, 400f. The Consuls made war on the Hernici (Liv. 7.9.1-2); one of them, probably Sulpicius, celebrated a triumph (Act. Tr., [-Ma]rt.; Degrassi 68f., 540)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/631> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #631" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the confusion in the dates of Calvus and Stolo, see 364, Consuls." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/614> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #614" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.2.1; Diod. 15.95.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -] Peticus; Licinius' name entire); Val. Max. 2.4.4; Plut. RQ 107; Chr. 354 (Petico et Calbo); Fast. Hyd. (Petito et Galba), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 32f., 104, 400f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/613> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #613" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Fast. Cap. Calvus was Cos. in 364 and Stolo in 361; in Livy, Val. Max. and Plut. their positions are reversed. On a similar confusion in our sources for the name of Licinius, the Mag. Eq. of 368, see 368, note 2. Sulpicius' praenomen T. in Livy is corrected from Cassiod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/597> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #597" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 6.39.3; 10.8.8; Fast. Cap. ([Pr]imus e plebe); cf. Plut. Cam. 39.5; Dio fr. 29; Degrassi 32f., 103f., 398f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/596> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #596" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. and Dio name him Stolo and identify him with the Tribune of the Plebs (cf. also Liv. 10.8.8, in a speech), but here Livy's phrase \"qui tribunus militum fuerat\" differentiates the Master of Horse from the Tribune of the Plebs in office and so makes it possible to identify him with Calvus who, according to the Fast. Cap., was Consul in 364, or according to Livy, in 361." .
